The investigation into JonBenet Ramsey's murder continues as authorities seek the killer.
Prosecutors received funding for the grand jury investigation, despite mounting costs.
A white bear dressed as Santa Claus emerged as a clue in the case, with investigators tracing its origins.
The Ramseys, under scrutiny, broke their silence to cooperate with prosecutors.
However, suspicions linger due to their initial reluctance to work with police.
Calls for a special prosecutor intensify amid accusations of mishandling the case.
The search for justice in JonBenet's tragic death remains ongoing, with the focus shifting to experienced prosecutors for resolution.
